TinyGPS++-based GPS Library for Arduino
A lightweight C++ wrapper around the popular TinyGPS++ library that parses NMEA sentences from a serial GPS receiver and exposes common data in human-readable strings.
🧰 Hardware Required

    Arduino (Uno, Nano, Mega, ESP8266, ESP32, etc.)
    Serial GPS receiver (NEO-6M, NEO-M8N, ATGM336H, etc.)
    2 free digital pins for SoftwareSerial (or use native Serial1/Serial2 on boards that have them)

🔧 Wiring
Table
Copy
GPS	Arduino (SoftwareSerial)
VCC	3.3 – 5 V
GND	GND
TX	D7 (RXPin)
RX	D8 (TXPin) via level-shifter if 5 V → 3.3 V
📦 Installation

    Arduino IDE → Library Manager
        Install TinyGPS++ by Mikal Hart
        Install SoftwareSerial (built-in on AVR; on ESP32 use HardwareSerial instead)
    Copy the files
        TinyGPSPlus.h, TinyGPSPlus.cpp → Documents/Arduino/libraries/TinyGPSPlus
        Drop this GPS.h (or rename it) into your sketch folder.


API Reference
Table
Copy
Method	Return	Description
begin(baud)	void	Starts the software-serial port. Default 9600 bps.
readData()	bool	true when a fresh TinyGPS++ fix is available.
generateMapLink()	String	OpenStreetMap URL: https://www.openstreetmap.org/?mlat=...&mlon=...&zoom=15
height()	String	Altitude in meters with 1 decimal place.
speed()	String	Ground speed in km/h (integer).
direction()	String	Course over ground in degrees (integer).
satellites()	String	Number of satellites in use.
hdop()	String	Horizontal Dilution of Precision.
date()	String	“MM/DD/YYYY” or “Not Available Date”.
time()	String	“HH:MM:SS” UTC or “Not Available Time”.
⚙️ Advanced Usage

    Change baud rate
    cpp

    Copy

    serialgps.begin(115200);   // if your module is pre-configured

    HardwareSerial on ESP32
    Replace SoftwareSerial gpsSerial(RXPin, TXPin); with HardwareSerial &gpsSerial = Serial2; and adjust pins via Serial2.begin(9600, SERIAL_8N1, 16, 17);.
    Custom zoom level
    Modify generateMapLink() to append &zoom=18 for closer view.

✅ Troubleshooting
Table
Copy
Symptom	Fix
“Not Available Time/Date”	Ensure the GPS has a clear sky view and a 3-D fix (≥ 4 satellites).
Garbage characters	Confirm TX/RX wiring and baud-rate match.
ESP8266 reboots	Use yield() inside the readData() while-loop or switch to HardwareSerial.
